<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-11-09T12:14:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-11-09T12:14:00-05:00" n="791" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d791">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">822.51 Et 3/12: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bading</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-11-09T12:00:00-05:14"><hi rend="italic">November 9,
                                        1923—12 noon</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received 11:55
                                p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>16. Department’s 17, November 6, 3 p.m. Department’s information
                            essentially correct. Full text mailed October 30th. Information <pb facs="1052" n="936" xml:id="pg_936"/> here indicates final contract
                            may not be signed. Strong opposition. President still in Guayaquil. Will
                            keep Department informed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bading</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>